This paper deals with the problem of identifying multiple contexts of an AUV model, which is a core problem in robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses long-short-term-memory (LSTM) networks to learn the different contexts directly from the data, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with classification accuracy, which is a common problem in machine learning, and hence it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the problem of disturbances to the system's dynamics, which is a common problem in control systems, and hence it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of simulation models and generating different model contexts, which could also fall under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as it deals with generating models from data.
